Civil servants have been asked to get new e-passports in four months or risk being blocked from travelling out of the country. Head of Public Service Joseph Kinyua said international travel clearances for public servants will only be granted to e-passport holders. The clearances involve both official or personal travels. "With effect from February 28, 2019, travel clearances for international travel by public servants will only be granted where applicant possess a Kenyan e-passport,‚Äù Kinyua said in a circular dated September 26. The move is to foster migration to the e-passport ahead of the August 31, deadline. Click here for the latest political news